          "username": "MichalJagielloTMPL"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-31 09:39:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nYou can also use dictionary config for setting up loggers. In settings file you can create a variable which can look like this:\n\nLOG_CONFIG = {\n    \"version\": 1,\n    \"disable_existing_loggers\": False,\n    \"formatters\": {\n        \"default\": {\n            \"class\": \"logging.Formatter\",\n            \"format\": \"%(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(lineno)d:%(filename)s(%(process)d) - %(message)s\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"handlers\": {\n        \"console\": {\n            \"level\": \"DEBUG\",\n            \"class\": \"logging.StreamHandler\",\n            \"formatter\": \"default\"\n        },\n        \"file\": {\n            \"level\": \"DEBUG\",\n            \"class\": \"logging.FileHandler\",\n            \"formatter\": \"default\",\n            \"filename\": \"./file_handler.log\",\n            \"mode\": \"w\"\n        }\n    },\n    \"root\": {\n        \"level\": \"DEBUG\",\n        \"handlers\": [\"console\", \"file\"]\n    }\n}\n\nand then just call \n\nimport logging.config\nfrom onapsdk.configuration import settings\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    logging.config.dictConfig(settings.LOG_CONFIG)\n\nEveryone who wants to change settings can simply override it in settings. You need to remember that with it you can't use `__init_subclass__` because code in `__main__` is calling later than `__init_subclass__` and logger created there won't use settings configuration",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
